sequenceDiagram
    participant User
    participant Orchestrator as Kubernetes Orchestrator
    participant K8s as Kubernetes API
    participant S3 as S3/MinIO Storage
    participant InitContainer as Init Container:<br/>hydrate-project
    participant PVC as Persistent Volume Claim<br/>(Block Storage)
    participant DevServer as Dev Container:<br/>npm run dev
    participant Cleanup as Cleanup CronJob

    Note over User,Cleanup: LAYER 1: HYDRATION (S3 → Local)

    User->>Orchestrator: POST /api/projects/{id}/start
    Orchestrator->>K8s: Create Deployment manifest
    K8s->>InitContainer: Start init container
    InitContainer->>S3: Check if project exists<br/>HEAD s3://bucket/projects/{uuid}.tar.gz

    alt Project exists in S3 (Hibernated)
        S3-->>InitContainer: 200 OK
        InitContainer->>S3: Download project tarball<br/>GET s3://bucket/projects/{uuid}.tar.gz
        S3-->>InitContainer: Project tarball (compressed)
        InitContainer->>InitContainer: Extract tarball
        InitContainer->>PVC: Write files to /workspace
        PVC-->>InitContainer: Files written
    else New project (No S3 backup)
        S3-->>InitContainer: 404 Not Found
        InitContainer->>InitContainer: Copy template files
        InitContainer->>PVC: Write template to /workspace
        PVC-->>InitContainer: Files written
    end

    InitContainer->>InitContainer: Set permissions<br/>chown -R node:node /workspace
    InitContainer->>K8s: Signal init complete
    K8s->>DevServer: Start main container

    Note over User,Cleanup: LAYER 2: RUNTIME (Fast Local I/O)

    DevServer->>PVC: Mount /workspace as volume
    PVC-->>DevServer: Volume mounted
    DevServer->>DevServer: npm install<br/>(reads/writes to PVC)
    DevServer->>DevServer: npm run dev<br/>(reads from PVC)
    DevServer->>DevServer: Vite compiles<br/>(reads/writes to PVC)

    User->>DevServer: Make code changes via agent/editor
    DevServer->>PVC: Write updated files
    PVC-->>DevServer: Files saved
    DevServer->>DevServer: Hot reload<br/>(reads from PVC)

    Note over PVC: All I/O happens on fast<br/>local block storage (EBS/local disk)<br/>NO network overhead during runtime

    User->>DevServer: Test application
    DevServer-->>User: Serve via Ingress

    Note over User,Cleanup: LAYER 3: DEHYDRATION (Local → S3)

    User->>Orchestrator: POST /api/projects/{id}/stop<br/>OR Idle timeout detected
    Orchestrator->>K8s: Delete Deployment<br/>OR Send SIGTERM
    K8s->>DevServer: Trigger PreStop hook

    DevServer->>DevServer: Run preStop script:<br/>/app/dehydrate.sh
    DevServer->>PVC: Read all files from /workspace
    PVC-->>DevServer: Project files
    DevServer->>DevServer: Create tarball:<br/>tar -czf project.tar.gz /workspace
    DevServer->>S3: Upload tarball<br/>PUT s3://bucket/projects/{uuid}.tar.gz
    S3-->>DevServer: Upload complete

    DevServer->>K8s: PreStop hook complete
    K8s->>DevServer: Send SIGKILL (grace period end)
    DevServer->>K8s: Pod terminated

    K8s->>PVC: Release volume claim
    K8s->>K8s: Delete PVC (optional)

    Note over S3: Project safely stored in S3<br/>Ready for next hydration cycle

    Note over User,Cleanup: CLEANUP CRONJOB (Idle Detection)

    loop Every 10 minutes
        Cleanup->>Orchestrator: Check for idle projects
        Orchestrator->>Orchestrator: Query DB for projects:<br/>last_activity > 30 mins ago<br/>AND status = "running"

        alt Project is idle
            Orchestrator->>K8s: Get pod for project
            K8s-->>Orchestrator: Pod info
            Orchestrator->>K8s: Trigger dehydration:<br/>Delete Deployment
            K8s->>DevServer: SIGTERM → PreStop hook
            DevServer->>S3: Upload project (as above)
            K8s->>K8s: Delete pod + PVC
            Orchestrator->>Orchestrator: Update DB:<br/>status = "stopped"<br/>hibernation_state = "dehydrated"
        else Project is active
            Orchestrator->>Orchestrator: Skip cleanup
        end
    end

    Note over S3,PVC: The "Sandwich" Layers:<br/>1. S3 (Cold Storage - Persistent)<br/>2. PVC (Hot Storage - Ephemeral)<br/>3. S3 (Cold Storage - Persistent)

    Note over User,Cleanup: Benefits:<br/>- Fast I/O during runtime (local PVC)<br/>- Cost-effective storage (S3 when idle)<br/>- Auto-scaling friendly (stateless pods)<br/>- Project persistence across restarts
